    "summary": "This paper reports local compressibility measurements in magic-angle twisted bilayer graphene aligned with hBN, showing eight fractional Chern insulator (FCI) states at fractional fillings of native Chern bands. The key result is that weak magnetic fields stabilize FCIs by improving the Berry-curvature distribution of the moiré bands, while nearby charge-density-wave and symmetry-broken Chern-insulator states compete and disappear as FCIs emerge.",
